Object-oriented language, portable, common in enterprise apps, can be verbose

Primitive type sizes:

| Type | Size |
| --- | --- |
| byte | 1 byte |
| boolean | JVM-dependent, commonly treated as 1 byte in arrays |
| char | 2 bytes |
| short | 2 bytes |
| int | 4 bytes |
| float | 4 bytes |
| long | 8 bytes |
| double | 8 bytes |

Java primitive numeric sizes are fixed across platforms. Object/reference sizes depend on the JVM.
